# NOTES:
# 1. check /etc/default/tlp for disabling bluetooth/wifi on startup
# laptop power saving done through tlp
# autodimming done through xset, check xset -q for settings
# avoid xf86-video-intel installation in regards to xbacklight
# use community `light` package for managing backlight

# 2. launch unclutter-xfixes at startup
# settings in /etc/default/unclutter
# $ unclutter --timeout 1

# 3. to refresh i3blocks on battery plug-in, need to add event-based script
# add it to /etc/udev/rules.d with run script and environment specified

# 4. enable ufw firewall at startup
# $ sudo systemctl enable ufw

# 5. for ssh, add option of adding key to agent upon validation
# that way no need to input key multiple times
# Host *
# 	AddKeysToAgent yes
# 	IdentityFile ~/.ssh/id_rsa
# also add SSH agent to user-based systemd launch, see https://wiki.archlinux.org/index.php/SSH_keys#Start_ssh-agent_with_systemd_user

# 6. live audio device changes between headsets
# install acpid and enable acpid.service
# check acpi_listen and add event in /etc/acpi/events
# Pass all events to our one handler script
# event=jack/*
# action=/home/shankar/.config/i3/scripts/refresh_i3blocks_audio.sh %e
# link to refresh i3blocks script with appropriate signal call

# 7. keep dmenu on lower versions to prevent breakages

# 8. remap to de keyboard mapping upon i3 restart
# exec_always --no-startup-id setxkbmap -layout de && pkill -RTMIN+11 i3blocks
# script unnecessary after setting default keyboard locale and mapping

# 9. When using light, add user go `video` group in order to circumvent sudo
# usage when executing commands

# 10. Move i3_cycle exact python script to binary location instead of default installer
# this solution is much faster than the other method

# 11. i3lock post-suspend requires sleep to prevent short real display
# this is updated in current i3lock post-sleep hook in systemd

# 12. To prevent no screen found error on `startx`, add graphics
# to early KMS start protocol, take note of adjustment in /etc/mkinitcpio.conf

# 13. Take note of files in .xinitrc, including disabling repeat on XF86 buttons to prevent input flood

# 14. Replace i3-lock with i3lock-fancy-rapid to leverage faster speeds

# 15. Install lts and latest kernel, set preference directly in grub for latest kernel

# 16. systemctl enable systemd-timesyncd.service, in order to sync times
